modules.description: Provides functions to load and validate X.509 trust anchors from a static certificate database. Operates on byte sequences and certificate structures parsed from DER-encoded data. Used to establish secure communication in MirageOS unikernels by verifying server certificates against known trusted roots.

Provides functions to create an X.509 certificate authenticator using revocation lists and hash whitelists, with trust anchors derived from NSS' certdata.txt. Works with X509.CRL.t lists, Digestif.hash' lists, and X509.Authenticator.t. Used to validate TLS connections against NSS-trusted certificates with custom revocation checks.
